 García Santo-Tomás makes a strong case that the rise of the novel cannot be fully understood without taking into account its relationship to the scientific discoveries of the period.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 22. Okt 2019) 0aLiterature and sciencezSpainxHistoryy17th century. 0aSciencezSpainxHistoryy17th century. 0aSpanish fictionyClassical period, 1500-1700xHistory and criticism. 4aBaroque. 4aGalileo Galilei. 4aSpain. 4aliterature. 4aoptics. 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018z978311063537940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226465876423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226465876.jpg  a978-3-11-063537-9  University of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles